# Ansible Quest Conventions

## Single-file architecture
- All game code lives in `index.html` — HTML, CSS, and JS in one file
- Quiz questions are the exception: they live in `questions.json`
- Audio < 100KB is Base64 inline; larger files go in `assets/`

## CSS hidden pattern
Every element that uses `.hidden` toggling MUST have its own CSS rule:
```css
#my-element.hidden { display: none; }
```
There is no global `.hidden` class. Missing this rule = element always visible.

## Scene coordinates
- Districts: Village x=-28, Township x=0, Fortress x=28 (all z=0)
- Building grid: cx±10, cz±9 relative to district center
- Horizontal road: z=14 world
- Never place objects inside building zones without checking `_buildingBoxes`

## State management
- Dead NPCs use `v.dead = true; v.mesh.visible = false` — never splice from arrays
- Respawn by resetting `dead = false; mesh.visible = true`
- Chest collection is tracked by `_chests[i].collected` flag

## UI overlays
- Always reset overlay state (buttons, quiz panels, success panels) when opening
- Escape key should go back one level, not jump to home
- Use `pointer-events: none` on disabled buttons, not just visual dimming
